name: API Call
type: Coordination/Source
description: |
  Source specialization describing a programmatic API request. An API Call source means the Timeline Provider or event
  source received the action through an API credential or programmatic integration rather than an interactive browser
  session. This distinction is important because many policies allow programmatic requests for low-risk or automated
  tasks but require an interactive principal actor for high-risk operations.

  The `apiKeyId` identifies the credential, integration, or client registration used for the request. It may be opaque to
  third parties, but it should be meaningful to the provider and account owner for audit, revocation, and incident
  investigation. A provider-specific API Call subtype may include additional fields such as client application,
  authentication strength, IP/session metadata, signing key reference, or delegation scope.

  API Call describes the transport/source of the request, not the actor category. A programmatic request may still be
  attributed to a Principal Actor if the credential is treated as direct principal control, or to an Agent Actor if the
  provider recognizes the caller as delegated automation. Actor Policy may combine both dimensions.
apiKeyId:
  type: Text
  description: Identifier of the API credential used for the request.
